      syntax: `## 4. 正解の根拠となるセンテンスの構文解析

<div style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: bold; color: #1e293b; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">A Slow Life in the Trees (過去問)</div>

<p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;"><span style="font-weight:bold; color:#000;">[Strategy Note]</span> 「対比 (Unlike)」と「因果関係 (Because/To...)」を正確に把握する力が問われます。</p>

<h4 class="syntax-question-header">【設問34の根拠】(正解: 3)</h4>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> ナマケモノがサルと違う点の1つは？<br><strong>A:</strong> たいてい単独で生活している。</p>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-evidence">
  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Evidence:</span> "However, <strong>unlike</strong> monkeys, sloths <strong>live</strong> alone, <strong>move</strong> very slowly..."
</div>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-structure">
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
    <li><strong>前置詞 (unlike):</strong> ～とは違って (Contrast marker)</li>
    <li><strong>動詞の列挙:</strong> live alone, move slowly, make no noise</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h4 class="syntax-question-header">【設問35の根拠】(正解: 1)</h4>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> ナマケモノがゆっくり動く理由の1つは？<br><strong>A:</strong> 使用するエネルギー量を減らすため。</p>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-evidence">
  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Evidence:</span> "By sleeping... and moving slowly, sloths <strong>do not have to use</strong> much energy."
</div>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-structure">
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
    <li><strong>手段 (By doing):</strong> By sleeping and moving slowly</li>
    <li><strong>結果:</strong> do not have to use much energy (エネルギーを使う必要がない)</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-point">
  "do not have to use" が選択肢の "reduce the amount" に対応します。
</div>

<h4 class="syntax-question-header">【設問36の根拠】(正解: 3)</h4>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> ワシや大型のネコ科動物は...<br><strong>A:</strong> 動物の動きを探すことによって狩りをする。</p>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-evidence">
  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Evidence:</span> "However, these hunters <strong>search for</strong> movement, so they often <strong>do not notice</strong> sloths."
</div>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-structure">
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
    <li><strong>主語 (these hunters):</strong> Eagles and big cats</li>
    <li><strong>動詞 (search for):</strong> ～を探す (hunt by looking for)</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h4 class="syntax-question-header">【設問37の根拠】(正解: 4)</h4>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> ナマケモノは長い爪を何に使うか？<br><strong>A:</strong> 枝にしがみつくのを助けるため。</p>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-evidence">
  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Evidence:</span> "Usually, they <strong>use</strong> their claws to <strong>hang on to</strong> branches."
</div>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-structure">
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
    <li><strong>不定詞 (to hang on):</strong> 目的 (～するために)</li>
    <li><strong>言い換え:</strong> hang on to -> hold on to</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<br><hr><br>

<div style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: bold; color: #1e293b; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Sleeping in the Eucalyptus (オリジナル)</div>

<p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;"><span style="font-weight:bold; color:#000;">[Strategy Note]</span> 過去問と同じく、生物の習性（理由）と身体的特徴（機能）を結びつける論理構成です。</p>

<h4 class="syntax-question-header">【設問1の根拠】(正解: 2)</h4>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> コアラがクマと違う点の1つは？<br><strong>A:</strong> 赤ちゃんを袋に入れて運ぶ。</p>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-evidence">
  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Evidence:</span> "However, <strong>unlike</strong> bears, koalas <strong>are</strong> marsupials, which means they <strong>carry</strong> their babies in a pouch."
</div>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-structure">
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
    <li><strong>前置詞 (unlike):</strong> 対比マーカー</li>
    <li><strong>関係代名詞 (which):</strong> marsupials の説明 (means they carry...)</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-point">
  "unlike bears" の直後の記述が正解の根拠になります。
</div>

<h4 class="syntax-question-header">【設問2の根拠】(正解: 3)</h4>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> コアラが長く眠る理由の1つは？<br><strong>A:</strong> 体が食べ物から毒を取り除くのを可能にするため。</p>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-evidence">
  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Evidence:</span> "Also, the leaves <strong>contain</strong> poison. Sleeping... <strong>gives</strong> the koala's body the time it needs to... <strong>remove</strong> the poison safely."
</div>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-structure">
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
    <li><strong>因果:</strong> Poison exists -> Sleeping gives time -> Remove poison</li>
    <li><strong>言い換え:</strong> remove the poison -> allow their bodies to remove poison</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h4 class="syntax-question-header">【設問3の根拠】(正解: 1)</h4>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> コアラがディンゴから安全な理由は？<br><strong>A:</strong> ディンゴは木に登ることができないから。</p>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-evidence">
  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Evidence:</span> "However, dingoes <strong>cannot climb</strong> trees, so they <strong>cannot reach</strong> the koalas."
</div>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-structure">
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
    <li><strong>理由 (so):</strong> (原因) cannot climb -> (結果) cannot reach (safe)</li>
  </ul>
</div>
<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-point">
  シンプルな因果関係ですが、"reach" が "safe" という概念に変換されています。
</div>

<h4 class="syntax-question-header">【設問4の根拠】(正解: 4)</h4>
<p><strong>Q:</strong> コアラは特別な前足を何に使うか？<br><strong>A:</strong> 木の枝にしっかりとしがみつくため。</p>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-evidence">
  <span style="font-weight:bold;">Evidence:</span> "They also <strong>have</strong> two thumbs... which <strong>help</strong> them <strong>hold onto</strong> smooth branches tightly."
</div>

<div class="syntax-panel syntax-panel-structure">
  <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem;">
    <li><strong>関係代名詞 (which):</strong> two thumbs (part of paws) の機能を説明</li>
    <li><strong>言い換え:</strong> hold onto tightly</li>
  </ul>
</div>`
